gtmAttrDownThreshold.description: Deprecated!. The down_threshold value. If a host server or a host virtual server has been marked down for the last down_threshold probing cycles (timer_get_host_data or timer_get_vs_data respectively), then perform service checks every down_multiple * timer period instead.

gtmAttrDownMultiple.name: gtmAttrDownMultiple
gtmAttrDownMultiple.description: Deprecated!. The down_multiple value. If a host server or a host virtual server has been marked down for the last down_threshold probing cycles (timer_get_host_data or timer_get_vs_data respectively), then perform service checks every down_multiple * timer period instead.

gtmAttrPathDuration.description: Deprecated!. The number of seconds that a path remains cached after its last access.

gtmAttrRttSampleCount.name: gtmAttrRttSampleCount
gtmAttrRttSampleCount.description: Deprecated!. The number of packets to send out in a probe request to determine path information.

gtmAttrRttPacketLength.name: gtmAttrRttPacketLength

gtmAttrRttTimeout.name: gtmAttrRttTimeout

gtmAttrMaxMonReqs.name: gtmAttrMaxMonReqs
gtmAttrMaxMonReqs.description: Deprecated!. The maximum synchronous monitor request, which is used to control the maximum number of monitor requests being sent out at one time for a given probing interval. This will allow the user to smooth out monitor probe requests as much as they desire.

gtmAttrTraceroutePort.name: gtmAttrTraceroutePort
gtmAttrTraceroutePort.description: Deprecated!. The port to use to collect traceroute (hops) data.

gtmAttrPathsNeverDie.name: gtmAttrPathsNeverDie
gtmAttrPathsNeverDie.description: Deprecated!. The state indicating whether the dynamic load balancing modes can use path data even after the TTL for the path data has expired.

gtmAttrProbeDisabledObjects.name: gtmAttrProbeDisabledObjects
gtmAttrProbeDisabledObjects.description: Deprecated!. The state indicating whether probing disabled objects by global traffic management object(GTM) is enabled or not.

gtmAttrLinkLimitFactor.name: gtmAttrLinkLimitFactor
gtmAttrLinkLimitFactor.description: Deprecated!. The link limit factor, which is used to set a target percentage for traffic. For example, if it is set to 90, the ratio cost based load-balancing will set a ratio with a maximum value equal to 90% of the limit value for the link. Default is 95%.

gtmAttrOverLimitLinkLimitFactor.name: gtmAttrOverLimitLinkLimitFactor
gtmAttrOverLimitLinkLimitFactor.description: Deprecated!. The over-limit link limit factor. If traffic on a link exceeds the limit, this factor will be used instead of the link_limit_factor until the traffic is over limit for more than max_link_over_limit_count times. Once the limit has been exceeded too many times, all traffic is shut off for the link. The default for over_limit_link_limit_factor is 90%.

gtmAttrLinkPrepaidFactor.name: gtmAttrLinkPrepaidFactor
gtmAttrLinkPrepaidFactor.description: Deprecated!. The link prepaid factor. Maximum percentage of traffic allocated to link which has a traffic allotment which has been prepaid. Default is 95%.

gtmAttrLinkCompensateInbound.name: gtmAttrLinkCompensateInbound
gtmAttrLinkCompensateInbound.description: Deprecated!. The link compensate inbound. If set, the link allotment calculation will take into account traffic which does not flow through the BIGIP, i.e. if more traffic is flowing through a link as measured by SNMP on the router than is flowing through the BIGIP. This applies to inbound traffic which the major volume will initiate from internal clients.

gtmAttrLinkCompensateOutbound.name: gtmAttrLinkCompensateOutbound
gtmAttrLinkCompensateOutbound.description: Deprecated!. The link compensate outbound. If set, the link allotment calculation will take into account traffic which does not flow through the BIGIP, i.e. if more traffic is flowing through a link as measured by SNMP on the router than is flowing through the BIGIP. This applies to outbound traffic which the major volume will initiate from internal clients.

gtmAttrMaxLinkOverLimitCount.name: gtmAttrMaxLinkOverLimitCount
gtmAttrMaxLinkOverLimitCount.description: Deprecated!. The maximum link over limit count. The count of how many times in a row traffic may be over the defined limit for the link before it is shut off entirely. Default is 1.

gtmAttrLowerBoundPctRow.name: gtmAttrLowerBoundPctRow
gtmAttrLowerBoundPctRow.description: Deprecated!. Deprecated! No longer useful. The lower bound percentage row option in Internet Weather Map.

gtmAttrLowerBoundPctCol.name: gtmAttrLowerBoundPctCol
gtmAttrLowerBoundPctCol.description: Deprecated!. Deprecated! No longer useful. The lower bound percentage column option in Internet Weather Map.

gtmAttrAutoconf.name: gtmAttrAutoconf
gtmAttrAutoconf.description: Deprecated!. The state indicating whether to auto configure BIGIP/3DNS servers (automatic addition and deletion of self IPs and virtual servers).

gtmAttrAutosync.name: gtmAttrAutosync
gtmAttrAutosync.description: Deprecated!. The state indicating whether or not to autosync. Allows automatic updates of wideip.conf to/from other 3-DNSes.

gtmAttrSyncNamedConf.name: gtmAttrSyncNamedConf
gtmAttrSyncNamedConf.description: Deprecated!. The state indicating whether or not to auto-synchronize named configuration. Allows automatic updates of named.conf to/from other 3-DNSes.

gtmAttrSyncGroup.name: gtmAttrSyncGroup
gtmAttrSyncGroup.description: Deprecated!. The name of sync group.

gtmAttrSyncTimeout.name: gtmAttrSyncTimeout
gtmAttrSyncTimeout.description: Deprecated!. The sync timeout. If synch'ing from a remote 3-DNS takes longer than this timeout, then abort the connection.

gtmAttrSyncZonesTimeout.name: gtmAttrSyncZonesTimeout
gtmAttrSyncZonesTimeout.description: Deprecated!. The sync zones timeout. If synch'ing named and zone configuration takes this timeout, then abort the connection.

gtmAttrTimeTolerance.name: gtmAttrTimeTolerance
gtmAttrTimeTolerance.description: Deprecated!. The allowable time difference for data to be out of sync between members of a sync group.

gtmAttrTopologyLongestMatch.name: gtmAttrTopologyLongestMatch
gtmAttrTopologyLongestMatch.description: Deprecated!. The state indicating whether or not the 3-DNS Controller selects the topology record that is most specific and, thus, has the longest match, in cases where there are several IP/netmask items that match a particular IP address. If it is set to false, the 3-DNS Controller uses the first topology record that matches (according to the order of entry) in the topology statement.

gtmAttrTopologyAclThreshold.name: gtmAttrTopologyAclThreshold
gtmAttrTopologyAclThreshold.description: Deprecated!. Deprecated! The threshold of the topology ACL. This is an outdated mechanism for disabling a node.

gtmAttrStaticPersistCidr.name: gtmAttrStaticPersistCidr
gtmAttrStaticPersistCidr.description: Deprecated!. The variable used with the static persistence load balancing mode to allow users to specify what cidr should be used. This is used for IPv4.

gtmAttrStaticPersistV6Cidr.name: gtmAttrStaticPersistV6Cidr
gtmAttrStaticPersistV6Cidr.description: Deprecated!. The variable used with the static persistence load balancing mode to allow users to specify what cidr should be used. This is used for IPv6.

gtmAttrQosFactorVsScore.name: gtmAttrQosFactorVsScore

gtmAttrTimerSendKeepAlive.name: gtmAttrTimerSendKeepAlive
gtmAttrTimerSendKeepAlive.description: Deprecated!. The frequency of GTM keep alive messages (strictly the config timestamps).

gtmWideipIpv6Noerror.name: gtmWideipIpv6Noerror

gtmWideipLoadBalancingDecisionLogVerbosi.name: gtmWideipLoadBalancingDecisionLogVerbosity
gtmWideipLoadBalancingDecisionLogVerbosi.description: The log verbosity value when making load-balancing decisions. From the least significant bit to the most significant bit, each bit represents enabling or disabling a certain load balancing log. When the first bit is 1, log will contain pool load-balancing algorithm details. When the second bit is 1, log will contain details of all pools traversed during load-balancing. When the third bit is 1, log will contain pool member load-balancing algorithm details. When the fourth bit is 1, log will contain details of all pool members traversed during load-balancing.

gtmWideipStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in gtmWideipStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

gtmAttr2DumpTopology.description: The state indicating whether or not to dump the topology.

gtmAttr2CacheLdns.name: gtmAttr2CacheLdns
gtmAttr2CacheLdns.description: The state indicating whether or not to cache LDNSes.

gtmAttr2AolAware.name: gtmAttr2AolAware
gtmAttr2AolAware.description: The state indicating whether or not local DNS servers that belong to AOL (America Online) are recognized.

gtmAttr2CheckStaticDepends.name: gtmAttr2CheckStaticDepends
gtmAttr2CheckStaticDepends.description: The state indicating whether or not to check the availability of virtual servers.

gtmAttr2CheckDynamicDepends.name: gtmAttr2CheckDynamicDepends
gtmAttr2CheckDynamicDepends.description: The state indicating whether or not to check availability of a path before it uses the path for load balancing.

gtmAttr2DrainRequests.name: gtmAttr2DrainRequests
gtmAttr2DrainRequests.description: The state indicating whether or not persistent connections are allowed to remain connected, until TTL expires, when disabling a pool.

gtmAttr2EnableResetsRipeness.name: gtmAttr2EnableResetsRipeness
gtmAttr2EnableResetsRipeness.description: The state indicating whether or not ripeness value is allowed to be reset.

gtmAttr2FbRespectDepends.name: gtmAttr2FbRespectDepends
gtmAttr2FbRespectDepends.description: The state indicating whether or not to respect virtual server status when load balancing switches to the fallback mode.

gtmAttr2FbRespectAcl.name: gtmAttr2FbRespectAcl
gtmAttr2FbRespectAcl.description: Deprecated! The state indicating whether or not to respect ACL. This is part of an outdated mechanism for disabling virtual servers

gtmAttr2PersistMask.name: gtmAttr2PersistMask
gtmAttr2PersistMask.description: Deprecated! Replaced by gtmAttrStaticPersistCidr and gtmAttrStaticPersistV6Cidr. The persistence mask which is used to determine the netmask applied for static persistance requests.

gtmAttr2GtmSetsRecursion.name: gtmAttr2GtmSetsRecursion
gtmAttr2GtmSetsRecursion.description: The state indicating whether set recursion by global traffic management object(GTM) is enable or not.

gtmAttr2QosFactorLcs.name: gtmAttr2QosFactorLcs
gtmAttr2QosFactorLcs.description: The factor used to normalize link capacity values when the load balancing mode is set to LB_METHOD_QOS.

gtmAttr2QosFactorRtt.name: gtmAttr2QosFactorRtt
gtmAttr2QosFactorRtt.description: The factor used to normalize round-trip time values when the load balancing mode is set to LB_METHOD_QOS.

gtmAttr2QosFactorHops.name: gtmAttr2QosFactorHops
gtmAttr2QosFactorHops.description: The factor used to normalize hops when the load balancing mode is set to LB_METHOD_QOS.

gtmAttr2QosFactorHitRatio.name: gtmAttr2QosFactorHitRatio
gtmAttr2QosFactorHitRatio.description: The factor used to normalize ping packet completion rates when the load balancing mode is set to LB_METHOD_QOS.

gtmAttr2QosFactorPacketRate.name: gtmAttr2QosFactorPacketRate
gtmAttr2QosFactorPacketRate.description: The factor used to normalize packet rates when the load balancing mode is set to LB_METHOD_QOS.

gtmAttr2QosFactorBps.name: gtmAttr2QosFactorBps
gtmAttr2QosFactorBps.description: The factor used to normalize kilobytes per second when the load balancing mode is set to LB_METHOD_QOS.

gtmAttr2QosFactorVsCapacity.name: gtmAttr2QosFactorVsCapacity
gtmAttr2QosFactorVsCapacity.description: The factor used to normalize virtual server capacity values when the load balancing mode is set to LB_METHOD_QOS.

gtmAttr2QosFactorTopology.name: gtmAttr2QosFactorTopology
gtmAttr2QosFactorTopology.description: The factor used to normalize topology values when the load balancing mode is set to LB_METHOD_QOS.

gtmAttr2QosFactorConnRate.name: gtmAttr2QosFactorConnRate
gtmAttr2QosFactorConnRate.description: Deprecated! Replaced by gtmAttrQosFactorVsScore. The factor used to normalize connection rates when the load balancing mode is set to LB_METHOD_QOS.

gtmAttr2TimerRetryPathData.name: gtmAttr2TimerRetryPathData
gtmAttr2TimerRetryPathData.description: The frequency at which to retrieve path data.

gtmAttr2TimerGetAutoconfigData.name: gtmAttr2TimerGetAutoconfigData
gtmAttr2TimerGetAutoconfigData.description: The frequency at which to retrieve auto-configuration data.

gtmAttr2TimerPersistCache.name: gtmAttr2TimerPersistCache
gtmAttr2TimerPersistCache.description: The frequency at which to retrieve path and metrics data from the system cache.

gtmAttr2DefaultProbeLimit.name: gtmAttr2DefaultProbeLimit
gtmAttr2DefaultProbeLimit.description: The default probe limit, the number of times to probe a path.

gtmAttr2DownThreshold.name: gtmAttr2DownThreshold
gtmAttr2DownThreshold.description: The down_threshold value. If a host server or a host virtual server has been marked down for the last down_threshold probing cycles (timer_get_host_data or timer_get_vs_data respectively), then perform service checks every down_multiple * timer period instead.

gtmAttr2DownMultiple.name: gtmAttr2DownMultiple
gtmAttr2DownMultiple.description: The down_multiple value. If a host server or a host virtual server has been marked down for the last down_threshold probing cycles (timer_get_host_data or timer_get_vs_data respectively), then perform service checks every down_multiple * timer period instead.

gtmAttr2PathTtl.name: gtmAttr2PathTtl
gtmAttr2PathTtl.description: The TTL for the path information.

gtmAttr2TraceTtl.name: gtmAttr2TraceTtl
gtmAttr2TraceTtl.description: The TTL for the traceroute information.

gtmAttr2LdnsDuration.name: gtmAttr2LdnsDuration
gtmAttr2LdnsDuration.description: The number of seconds that an inactive LDNS remains cached.

gtmAttr2PathDuration.name: gtmAttr2PathDuration
gtmAttr2PathDuration.description: The number of seconds that a path remains cached after its last access.

gtmAttr2RttSampleCount.name: gtmAttr2RttSampleCount
gtmAttr2RttSampleCount.description: The number of packets to send out in a probe request to determine path information.

gtmAttr2RttPacketLength.name: gtmAttr2RttPacketLength
gtmAttr2RttPacketLength.description: The length of the packet sent out in a probe request to determine path information.

gtmAttr2RttTimeout.name: gtmAttr2RttTimeout
gtmAttr2RttTimeout.description: The timeout for RTT, in seconds.

gtmAttr2MaxMonReqs.name: gtmAttr2MaxMonReqs
gtmAttr2MaxMonReqs.description: The maximum synchronous monitor request, which is used to control the maximum number of monitor requests being sent out at one time for a given probing interval. This will allow the user to smooth out monitor probe requests as much as they desire.

gtmAttr2TraceroutePort.name: gtmAttr2TraceroutePort
gtmAttr2TraceroutePort.description: The port to use to collect traceroute (hops) data.

gtmAttr2PathsNeverDie.name: gtmAttr2PathsNeverDie
gtmAttr2PathsNeverDie.description: The state indicating whether the dynamic load balancing modes can use path data even after the TTL for the path data has expired.

gtmAttr2ProbeDisabledObjects.name: gtmAttr2ProbeDisabledObjects
gtmAttr2ProbeDisabledObjects.description: The state indicating whether probing disabled objects by global traffic management object(GTM) is enabled or not.

gtmAttr2LinkLimitFactor.name: gtmAttr2LinkLimitFactor
gtmAttr2LinkLimitFactor.description: The link limit factor, which is used to set a target percentage for traffic. For example, if it is set to 90, the ratio cost based load-balancing will set a ratio with a maximum value equal to 90% of the limit value for the link. Default is 95%.

gtmAttr2OverLimitLinkLimitFactor.name: gtmAttr2OverLimitLinkLimitFactor
gtmAttr2OverLimitLinkLimitFactor.description: The over-limit link limit factor. If traffic on a link exceeds the limit, this factor will be used instead of the link_limit_factor until the traffic is over limit for more than max_link_over_limit_count times. Once the limit has been exceeded too many times, all traffic is shut off for the link. The default for over_limit_link_limit_factor is 90%.

gtmAttr2LinkPrepaidFactor.name: gtmAttr2LinkPrepaidFactor
gtmAttr2LinkPrepaidFactor.description: The link prepaid factor. Maximum percentage of traffic allocated to link which has a traffic allotment which has been prepaid. Default is 95%.

gtmAttr2LinkCompensateInbound.name: gtmAttr2LinkCompensateInbound
gtmAttr2LinkCompensateInbound.description: The link compensate inbound. If set, the link allotment calculation will take into account traffic which does not flow through the BIGIP, i.e. if more traffic is flowing through a link as measured by SNMP on the router than is flowing through the BIGIP. This applies to inbound traffic which the major volume will initiate from internal clients.

gtmAttr2LinkCompensateOutbound.name: gtmAttr2LinkCompensateOutbound
gtmAttr2LinkCompensateOutbound.description: The link compensate outbound. If set, the link allotment calculation will take into account traffic which does not flow through the BIGIP, i.e. if more traffic is flowing through a link as measured by SNMP on the router than is flowing through the BIGIP. This applies to outbound traffic which the major volume will initiate from internal clients.

gtmAttr2MaxLinkOverLimitCount.name: gtmAttr2MaxLinkOverLimitCount
gtmAttr2MaxLinkOverLimitCount.description: The maximum link over limit count. The count of how many times in a row traffic may be over the defined limit for the link before it is shut off entirely. Default is 1.

gtmAttr2LowerBoundPctRow.name: gtmAttr2LowerBoundPctRow
gtmAttr2LowerBoundPctRow.description: Deprecated! No longer useful. The lower bound percentage row option in Internet Weather Map.

gtmAttr2LowerBoundPctCol.name: gtmAttr2LowerBoundPctCol
gtmAttr2LowerBoundPctCol.description: Deprecated! No longer useful. The lower bound percentage column option in Internet Weather Map.

gtmAttr2Autoconf.name: gtmAttr2Autoconf
gtmAttr2Autoconf.description: The state indicating whether to auto configure BIGIP/3DNS servers (automatic addition and deletion of self IPs and virtual servers).

gtmAttr2Autosync.name: gtmAttr2Autosync
gtmAttr2Autosync.description: The state indicating whether or not to autosync. Allows automatic updates of wideip.conf to/from other 3-DNSes.

gtmAttr2SyncNamedConf.name: gtmAttr2SyncNamedConf
gtmAttr2SyncNamedConf.description: The state indicating whether or not to auto-synchronize named configuration. Allows automatic updates of named.conf to/from other 3-DNSes.

gtmAttr2SyncTimeout.name: gtmAttr2SyncTimeout
gtmAttr2SyncTimeout.description: The sync timeout. If synch'ing from a remote 3-DNS takes longer than this timeout, then abort the connection.

gtmAttr2SyncZonesTimeout.name: gtmAttr2SyncZonesTimeout
gtmAttr2SyncZonesTimeout.description: The sync zones timeout. If synch'ing named and zone configuration takes this timeout, then abort the connection.

gtmAttr2TimeTolerance.name: gtmAttr2TimeTolerance
gtmAttr2TimeTolerance.description: The allowable time difference for data to be out of sync between members of a sync group.

gtmAttr2TopologyLongestMatch.name: gtmAttr2TopologyLongestMatch
gtmAttr2TopologyLongestMatch.description: The state indicating whether or not the 3-DNS Controller selects the topology record that is most specific and, thus, has the longest match, in cases where there are several IP/netmask items that match a particular IP address.
